ZH: 1. 大雨过后，房子的屋顶塌下来了。
EN: 1. After the heavy rain, the roof of the house collapsed.

ZH: 2. 那座桥因为年久失修，塌下来了。
EN: 2. The bridge collapsed due to long-term lack of maintenance.

ZH: 3. 地震发生后，许多建筑物都塌下来了。
EN: 3. Many buildings collapsed after the earthquake.

ZH: 4. 这座山坡很陡，山石很容易塌下来。
EN: 4. The hillside is very steep, and rocks easily collapse.

ZH: 5. 工地上的土坑突然塌下来，掩埋了几名工人。
EN: 5. The pit on the construction site suddenly collapsed, burying several workers.

ZH: 6. 雪弄得屋顶坍塌了。
EN: 6. The snow caused the roof to cave in.

ZH: 7. 这栋旧楼已经废弃很久了，随时都可能塌下来。
EN: 7. This old building has been abandoned for a long time and could collapse at any moment.

ZH: 8. 街道上的道路塌下来了，造成了交通堵塞。
EN: 8. The road on the street collapsed, causing traffic congestion.

ZH: 9. 过了几分钟，他腿上的椅子突然塌下来了。
EN: 9. After a few minutes, the chair he was sitting on suddenly collapsed.

ZH: 10. 这座桥梁的基础不稳固，所以容易塌下来。
EN: 10. The foundation of this bridge is not stable, so it is prone to collapse.

ZH: 11. 那家工厂因为火灾发生后，全部厂房都塌下来了。
EN: 11. After the fire broke out in the factory, all the buildings collapsed.

ZH: 12. 他们的计划全部塌下来了，所以需要重新开始。
EN: 12. Their plans all fell through, so they need to start over.

ZH: 13. 这片沼泽地上的地面很不稳，一不小心就会塌下来。
EN: 13. The ground in this marsh is very unstable, and it can easily give way.

ZH: 14. 他歪歪扭扭地坐下后，椅子轰然塌下来。
EN: 14. After he sat down crookedly, the chair collapsed with a bang.

ZH: 15. 这种建筑材料质量差，容易塌下来。
EN: 15. This kind of building material has poor quality and is prone to collapse.

ZH: 16. 那片冰因为高温融化，整个湖面塌下来了。
EN: 16. The ice on the lake collapsed entirely as a result of high temperature melting.

ZH: 17. 这栋楼的地基不牢固，随时可能会塌下来。
EN: 17. The foundation of this building is not solid and could collapse at any time.

ZH: 18. 当他一踩上门槛时，门突然塌下来了。
EN: 18. As he stepped on the doorstep, the door suddenly collapsed.

ZH: 19. 那个小女孩躲在房间里，因为她怕隔壁的墙塌下来。
EN: 19. The little girl hid in her room because she was afraid the wall next door would collapse.

ZH: 20. 在地震过后，整条街道的建筑物一个接一个地塌下来。
EN: 20. After the earthquake, the buildings on the entire street collapsed one after another.
